A CHARITY shop manager is running the Great Scottish Run to raise much-needed funds for Shelter Scotland. Charity shop boss runs to raise funds A CHARITY shop manager is running the Great Scottish Run to raise much-needed funds for Shelter Scotland.Sinead McLaughlin, manager of the Shelter Scotland shop in Douglas Street, Milngavie, will be running the 10K on October 5 to raise money for the housing and homelessness charity.Sinead will join 10,000 others through the centre of Glasgow and past the city's landmarks.